article.headline: SE Louisiana 63, Tex San Antonio 54
article.story: SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- Ricky Woods scored 16 points and Southeastern Louisiana rallied from a 13-point deficit to beat Texas-San Antonio 63-54 on Saturday. Souteastern Louisiana (14-6, 6-1 Southland) outscored Texas-San Antonio (9-8, 4-2) 12-2 in the final 4:48. Andre Owens scored 15 points for the Roadrunners and Raphael Posey and Anthony Fuqua each had 11. Texas-San Antonio went on a 15-2 run to start the second half and led 40-27 with 14:18 remaining. But the Roadrunners could only muster five field goals the rest of the way. After falling behind by 13, the Lions scored the next nine points and then rallied to tie the score at 49 with eight minutes left. Jonathan Patton hit a 3-pointer that gave Southeastern Louisiana the lead for good at 54-52 with 4:48 remaining. Nate Lofton and Terry Bryant each scored 12 points for the Lions.
